William T. Monahan  Independent Director, The Mosaic CompanyAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 5 Board Members in 5 different organizations across 9 different industries.See Board Relationships69$266,286
Background

		Mr. William T. Monahan, also known as Bill, has been the President of Business Forensics since June 2004. Mr. Monahan served as the Chairman of the Board of Imation Corp. from March 1996 to 2004, Chief Executive Officer from June 1996 to May 2004 and President March 1996 to June 2004. He served as an Interim Chief Executive Officer of Novelis Inc. from August 29, 2006 to January 2, 2007 and Non Executive Chairman since May 1, 2006. From June 1993 to March 1996, he served ... as Group Vice President, responsible for Electro and Communications Group of 3M and served as Senior Managing Director of 3M Italy from May 1992 to May 1993 and also served as its President. From September 1989 to May 1992, he served as Vice President of the Data Storage Products Division of 3M. He serves as a Director of Southwall Technologies Inc. He has been an Independent Director at The Mosaic Company since October 2004. He has been an Independent Director of Pentair plc (formerly Pentair Ltd.) since 2001 and its Lead Director since January 1, 2008. He serves as a Director of Oakleaf Waste Management, LLC and National Multiple Sclerosis Society. He has been a Trustee at National Multiple Sclerosis Society since November 2011. He served as an Independent Director of Hutchinson Technology Inc. from 2000 to January 30, 2013. He served as Director of Solutia Inc. from March 2008 to July 2, 2012 and its Lead Director until July 2, 2012. He served as a Non-independent & Non-executive Director at Novelis Inc. from 2005 to 2007. Mr. Monahan served as a Director of Imation Corp. since March 1996.Read Full Background




